Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane has laid criminal charges with the police over the leaking of a provisional Absa report.The Public Protector wants to find out how the leak occurred and who was behind it&sbquo; 702 reported.The provisional report into the bailout for Bankorp by the Reserve Bank was leaked to the Mail &amp; Guardian&sbquo; which published the report&rsquo;s contents on Friday.Mkhwebane said remedial action should include that Absa pay R2.25bn to the fiscus if her finding is upheld.She also recommended that the president consider a commission of inquiry into state looting during apartheid.Absa said on Friday it accept Mkhwebane&rsquo;s invitation to make further submissions in terms of the Public Protector Act.&ldquo;These submissions will correct several factual and legal inaccuracies that are contained in the Provisional Report. This will be done on or before the deadline of 28 February 2016.&rdquo;- TMG Digital